**Step 1: Identify amplitude and period.**

- Amplitude $= |2| = 2$

- Period $= \dfrac{2\pi}{3}$

**Step 2: Find the key points.**

One cycle goes from $x = 0$ to $x = \dfrac{2\pi}{3}$. The quarter-points 
divide this into four equal parts of length $\dfrac{2\pi/3}{4} = \dfrac{\pi}{6}$.

| $x$ | $y = 2\sin(3x)$ |
| $0$ | $2\sin(0) = 0$ |
| $\frac{\pi}{6}$ | $2\sin(\frac{\pi}{2}) = 2$ |
| $\frac{\pi}{3}$ | $2\sin(\pi) = 0$ |
| $\frac{\pi}{2}$ | $2\sin(\frac{3\pi}{2}) = -2$ |
| $\frac{2\pi}{3}$ | $2\sin(2\pi) = 0$ |

**Step 3: Plot and connect.**

center
tikzpicture[scale=1.8]
 % Axes
 (-0.2,0) – (2.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-2.5) – (0,2.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Grid
 (0.52,-2) – (0.52,2);
 (1.05,-2) – (1.05,2);
 (1.57,-2) – (1.57,2);
 (2.09,-2) – (2.09,2);
 (-0.1,2) – (2.3,2);
 (-0.1,-2) – (2.3,-2);

 % Curve

 plot (, {2*sin(3* r)});

 % Key points
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (1.5pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (0.52,2) circle (1.5pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (1.05,0) circle (1.5pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (1.57,-2) circle (1.5pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (2.09,0) circle (1.5pt);

 % Labels
 at (0.52,-0.25) { $\frac{\pi}{6}$};
 at (1.05,-0.25) { $\frac{\pi}{3}$};
 at (1.57,-0.25) { $\frac{\pi}{2}$};
 at (2.09,-0.25) { $\frac{2\pi}{3}$};
 at (-0.15,2) { $2$};
 at (-0.2,-2) { $-2$};
tikzpicture
center

**Step 1: Identify the transformations.**

- Amplitude: $2$

- Period: $\dfrac{2\pi}{1} = 2\pi$

- Phase shift: $\dfrac{\pi}{2}$ right

- Vertical shift: up $1$ (midline $y = 1$)

**Step 2: Find starting point and key points.**

For $y = \cos x$, the cycle starts at a maximum. With phase shift 
$\frac{\pi}{2}$ right, this cycle starts at $x = \frac{\pi}{2}$.

Key points (one period):

| $x$ | $y$ |
| $\frac{\pi}{2}$ | $2(1) + 1 = 3$ (max) |
| $\pi$ | $2(0) + 1 = 1$ (midline) |
| $\frac{3\pi}{2}$ | $2(-1) + 1 = -1$ (min) |
| $2\pi$ | $2(0) + 1 = 1$ (midline) |
| $\frac{5\pi}{2}$ | $2(1) + 1 = 3$ (max) |

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 % Axes
 (-0.5,0) – (9,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-2) – (0,4) node[above] {$y$};

 % Midline
 (-0.3,1) – (8.5,1);
 at (-0.5,1) { $1$};

 % Curve

 plot (, {2*cos(( - 1.57) r) + 1});

 % Key points
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (1.57,3) circle (3pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (3.14,1) circle (3pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (4.71,-1) circle (3pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (6.28,1) circle (3pt);
 lldraw[AtlasTeal] (7.85,3) circle (3pt);

 % Labels
 at (1.57,-0.5) { $\frac{\pi}{2}$};
 at (3.14,-0.5) { $\pi$};
 at (4.71,-0.5) { $\frac{3\pi}{2}$};
 at (6.28,-0.5) { $2\pi$};
 at (-0.4,3) { $3$};
 at (-0.5,-1) { $-1$};
tikzpicture
center

**Period:** $\dfrac{\pi}{2}$ (since $B = 2$)

**Asymptotes:** Where $2x = \dfrac{\pi}{2} + n\pi$, i.e., 
$x = \dfrac{\pi}{4} + \dfrac{n\pi}{2}$.

The asymptotes occur at $x = \pm\dfrac{\pi}{4}, \pm\dfrac{3\pi}{4}, \ldots$

